parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Automatic Seat Belt Restraint System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the automatic seat belt restraint system can cause injuries or fatalities in the event of a collision, as the passengers may not be properly restrained.
symptoms: The automatic seat belts stay in the unlocked position
the automatic seat belts do not engage when the ignition is turned on
the driver's side automatic shoulder belts do not work
the motorized shoulder belts move in track/tighten after closing the door
the lower portion of the shoulder belt gets caught in the lower reel assembly.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Intermittent Engine Stalling and Failure to Start
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent engine stalling and failure to start can cause unexpected loss of power while driving, increasing the risk of accidents, and leaving the driver stranded. This issue can also lead to inconvenience and disruption of daily activities.
symptoms: The engine dies while driving
the engine shuts off without warning
the engine RPMs drop to 0
the engine stalls and restarts while coasting
the engine fails to start
the engine starts after waiting for 10-15 minutes or longer.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the distributor and ignition system can cause the engine to stall or fail to start, leading to unexpected loss of power while driving, increasing the risk of accidents, and leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine dies while driving
the engine shuts off without warning
the engine RPMs drop to 0
the engine stalls and restarts while coasting
the engine fails to start
the distributor bearing fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The suspected issues with the fuel intake system can cause the engine to fail to start, leading to inconvenience and disruption of daily activities.
symptoms: The car won't start in high temperatures
the car starts after waiting for 20-30 minutes or longer
the car is not necessarily okay for trips after starting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The poor solder job on the main relays can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, especially in hot weather, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle turns over but doesn't start
the RPM starts to go down slowly and then shuts off
the vehicle takes a long time to turn on again
the vehicle stalls while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the distributor can cause damage to the timing belt and cam shafts, leading to costly repairs and potentially causing the engine to stall or fail.
symptoms: The engine stalls or fails
the timing belt is damaged
the cam shafts are damaged.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Water Ingress into Engine Air Intake
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water entering the engine air intake can cause severe engine damage, leading to costly repairs and potentially causing the engine to fail or stall.
symptoms: Water enters the engine air intake
severe engine damage occurs
the engine stalls or fails.
